         <div xml:id="alalal-h78521"><!-- l4d20a2 -->
            <head xml:id="alalal-h78521-Hd1e99">Articulus 2</head>
            <head xml:id="alalal-h78521-Hd1e101" type="question-title">An sanus poenitens potest conjicere de
certitudine charitatis, an odio an
amore dignus sit ?</head>
            <p xml:id="alalal-h78521-d1e104">
               <cb ed="#Be" n="b"/>
               <lb ed="#Be" n="35"/>ARTICULUS II.
<lb ed="#Be" n="36"/>An sanus poenitens potest conjicere de
<lb ed="#Be" n="37"/>certitudine charitatis, an odio an
<lb ed="#Be" n="38"/>amore dignus sit ?
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-h78521-d1e117">
               <lb ed="#Be" n="39"/>Deinde queritur de hoc quod dicit,
<lb ed="#Be" n="40"/>ibi, A, paulo post : <quote xml:id="alalal-h78521-Qd1e123"> Tene certum, et
<lb ed="#Be" n="41"/>dimitte incertum. </quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-h78521-d1e129">
               <lb ed="#Be" n="42"/>ConTRA:
<lb ed="#Be" n="43"/>Eccle. rx, 1 : <quote xml:id="alalal-h78521-Qd1e135">Nescit homo utrum 
amo<lb break="no" ed="#Be" n="44"/>re an odio dignus sit</quote>. Ergo poenitens et
<lb ed="#Be" n="45"/>confitens sanus; non est certus.
</p>
            <p xml:id="alalal-h78521-d1e144">
               <lb ed="#Be" n="46"/>Responsio. Intelligit hoc de certitudine
<lb ed="#Be" n="47"/>conjecture : quia conjicere potest de
<lb ed="#Be" n="48"/>amore charitatis, quando poenitet sanus :
<lb ed="#Be" n="49"/>sed signum est timoris tantum, quando .
<lb ed="#Be" n="50"/>non pcenitet nisi infirmus. Ecclesiastes
<lb ed="#Be" n="51"/>autem loquitur de certitudine scientiae :
<lb ed="#Be" n="52"/>hanc enim nullus habet.
</p>
         </div>
